I actually didn't hit any bad shots, to be honest with you.   The wind was into us on 5.   And I hit a good shot and it blew it to the right, into a spot where you can't hit it.   I knew I had a few birdie holes coming up.  
And then the back nine, a couple of par‑5s, mentally I'm getting better because that stuff doesn't bother me as much as I used to.   It's good to not get really hostile when you're battling in a tournament, which I used to do.  
   
